Done. Epic 7.5 (Offline Storage and Operations) has been broken into **20 user stories** organized by recommended build order:

**Foundation (stories 1–2):** Operation record persistence, optimistic UI updates

**Replay engine (stories 3–5):** Single operation replay, priority ordering, batch replay with fallback

**Error handling (stories 6–8):** Transient retry, permanent failure handling, conflict resolution

**Queue optimization (story 9):** Duplicate suppression

**Offline reading (stories 10–12):** Metadata storage, body/attachment storage, unavailable-offline indication

**Send flow (story 13):** Queue outgoing mail while offline

**Queue management UI (stories 14–18):** Operations view, cancel with revert, cancel queued send, bulk clear, status indicator

**Multi-account & protocol (stories 19–20):** Parallel per-account processing, protocol-aware routing

Each story follows the template with Parent Feature, User Story, Acceptance Criteria, Complexity, Blocked by (referencing sibling stories by filename), HITL/AFK classification, and Notes for ambiguities.
